President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. has declared a major disaster in the State of Louisiana and ordered federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts following severe winter storms from February 11 to February 19, 2021. The declaration makes federal funding available to affected individuals in multiple parishes. Assistance can include grants for temporary housing and home repairs, low-cost loans for uninsured property losses, and other programs to aid in recovery. Federal funding is also available for emergency protective measures and hazard mitigation measures statewide. John E. Long has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further damage assessments may result in additional designations.